{
  "doc_id": "19439",
  "text": "During asymmetric cell division in embryogenesis, the activity of Notch is biologically antagonized by the cell fate determinant Numb [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, Numb is also expressed in many adult mammalian cells [CITATION_3] , where it does not display asymmetrical partitioning at mitosis, suggesting additional functions. We reasoned that if the Numb/Notch antagonism is relevant to control of the proliferative/differentiative balance in the normal mammary parenchyma, then subversion of the Numb-mediated regulation of Notch might play a causative role in naturally occurring breast cancers. The present work was undertaken to test this possibility.",
